race.comment: BRUCKHEIMER (2) lined up for the tenth time and recorded his sixth minor placing when narrowly defeated last start over 1000m at the Sunshine Coast. Starting to test the patience but this extra trip at the third run back looks ideal. Must win one soon. STAR VENTURE (7) was beaten under two lengths when fresh from a spell over 1000m at Kembla recently. Won't find this as tough and the extra furlong helps. Genuine contender. TIDAL POINT (14) found 1000m a bit slick when resuming at the Sunshine Coast last start. Draws a far better gate and drops four kilos under this scale so she is worth an each-way wager. NIGHTLINE (12) debuts. Last seen trialling behind the talented Profoundly who shapes as a Best Bet at Doomben today.
